    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1449511188" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1449511188" />
    <a title="Kat" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11356755-kat"><img alt="Kat" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1514801647p2/11356755.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1449511188?book_show_action=true">Nov 22, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kat" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kat" href="/user/show/11356755-kat">Kat</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780973061925" href="/book/show/27418043-mother-teresa-s-advice-for-jilted-lovers">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11356755-kat?shelf=arr">arr</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1449511188" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5498593561796266906"><b>Advance Reader&apos;s Copy was given by the author in exchange for my honest review. </b><br/><br/><br/>The thing that caught my attention and made me curious about this book is the synopsis of the story of Tara and how every boyfriend she&apos;ve had died without her doing anything. At first I was like, &quot;Is this a paranormal or something?&quot; and &quot;This story is so weird, different and confusing but still, it seems interesting.&quot; Also, what caught my attention the most is the <b>&quot;rebel romance&quot;</b> description Donna gave to this book.</span>
  <span id="freeText5498593561796266906" style="display:none"><b>Advance Reader's Copy was given by the author in exchange for my honest review. </b><br /><br /><br />The thing that caught my attention and made me curious about this book is the synopsis of the story of Tara and how every boyfriend she've had died without her doing anything. At first I was like, "Is this a paranormal or something?" and "This story is so weird, different and confusing but still, it seems interesting." Also, what caught my attention the most is the <b>"rebel romance"</b> description Donna gave to this book. I mean, what's that, right? It was new to my ears 'cause I've never heard of it. So when Donna offered and asked for reviews to this book, I agreed immediately. What could go wrong trying out a different genre, right? <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><b>Tara's wondering why her ex boyfriends were suddenly dying without her doing anything to kill them. When she told her best friend, Betsy, about it, she figured it was because she might have some kind power. Later on, Betsy then realized that Tara's power could help other women and could get them a lot of cash too. So, Betsy's idea? Create a website wherein Tara gives advice to women who are in desperate need of help and a really really good advice to follow and people pay for it. <br /><i>Secrets are revealed and friendship gets broken. </i> </b><br /><br /><br /><br />Guess what? I was right! This is one heck of a great and interesting book! At first, I thought the pacing of the book was really slow but as I went on, I realized how much important these details were! It was so creative and fresh! Nothing I've ever read before! Now that's a great book! <br /><br /><br /><br />I have this love &amp; hate thing to Betsy's character at first. Her straightforwardness is great but the way she pressures Tara most of the time is annoying and ugh! But as the story went by, I seriously <b>hate</b> her! Why? <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Well, the fact that she lied to Tara and accusing her of killing her ex boyfriends pisses me off since she's the one who did those things. Ugh! I knew from the start that something was really wrong with her character.  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br />You know what I loved the most about this book? The dreams! Yes, the dreams-the vision Tara has to solve the problem! It's just so amazing! But quite heavy to deal with since it's a big responsibility and I don't like those kinds of big responsibilities.<br /><br /><br />I am so looking forward in reading the next book (if there is)! I was not satisfied with the ending! What happened next?! <br />So, I think that explains the lack of 1 star. But overall, it's a really good read! I recommend it to those who are looking for new books to read and want one that has a "different kind of genre"<br /><br />Thank you, Donna for giving me a chance to read and review your book!</span>
  <a data-text-id="5498593561796266906" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


