<span id="freeTextContainer12793849857016323122">I was given a copy of this book for an honest review.<br/>Wow! I certainly didn&apos;t expect that! I read this book in one sitting. I thought I was going to read a &apos;traditional romance&apos;, well I was certainly wrong. Donna has a way of writing that captivates you, and transports you into her story so fully that it is almost impossible to pull your kindle away from your face.<br/>Tara Holland has had really bad luck with men. Her past three lovers have all ended up dead. According to her best friend Betsy, Tara </span>
  <span id="freeText12793849857016323122" style="display:none">I was given a copy of this book for an honest review.<br />Wow! I certainly didn't expect that! I read this book in one sitting. I thought I was going to read a 'traditional romance', well I was certainly wrong. Donna has a way of writing that captivates you, and transports you into her story so fully that it is almost impossible to pull your kindle away from your face.<br />Tara Holland has had really bad luck with men. Her past three lovers have all ended up dead. According to her best friend Betsy, Tara had some sort of connection to the universe and was killing them without even knowing about it. <br />As I was reading I was thinking "this best friend is crazy in the head". I didn't expect the turn of events, that actually Tara did have some sort of connection to the universe. She was all for using it for good. Cue Betsy to make money off it. Betsy clearly was using Tara to her own advantage. The twist that came towards the end was so unexpected it actually made me gasp! This whole book is full of twists and turns. I won't go into to much detail because I don't want to ruin the book for you. But I will say that if you fancy a very different and quirky read then this book is for you! if not then you still need to read this book!</span>
