    <a title="Danielle Fisher" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23773611-danielle-fisher"><img alt="Danielle Fisher" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1445461046p2/23773611.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1444169578?book_show_action=true">Nov 16, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Danielle Fisher" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Danielle Fisher" href="/user/show/23773611-danielle-fisher">Danielle Fisher</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780973061925" href="/book/show/27418043-mother-teresa-s-advice-for-jilted-lovers">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1444169578" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8495823134590728315">Thanks goes out to Barker for providing me with an ARC in exchange for an honest review.<br/><br/>This book started off very strong. I was hooked and engaged with the unique storytelling, interesting plot line, and engaging questions that I really wanted to continue to read to learn the answers to. I thought the characters were well-developed, the plot was strong and, for the most part, the book had a steady pace to it.<br/><br/>So why the loss of a star? Unfortunately, the best friend really did not sit well with </span>
  <span id="freeText8495823134590728315" style="display:none">Thanks goes out to Barker for providing me with an ARC in exchange for an honest review.<br /><br />This book started off very strong. I was hooked and engaged with the unique storytelling, interesting plot line, and engaging questions that I really wanted to continue to read to learn the answers to. I thought the characters were well-developed, the plot was strong and, for the most part, the book had a steady pace to it.<br /><br />So why the loss of a star? Unfortunately, the best friend really did not sit well with me. In fact, I didn't see a single redeeming quality for most of the book. This is a very difficult personality clash when she was such a loud voice in the script. Again, COMPLETELY subjective. Barker is a strong writer who builds even stronger worlds and three dimensional characters, but there are certain characters that the reader may not mesh with. That has absolutely nothing to do with the author's writing ability or overall execution of the story line and plot, it's just a subjective opinion of a single reader.<br /><br />I would recommend to readers interested in contemporary fiction and open to alternative practices, like meditation, crystals, and psychic perception. A great read!<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="8495823134590728315" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


