<div id="review_3236634650" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3236634650" />
    <a title="W.L. Hawkin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/60316715-w-l-hawkin"><img alt="W.L. Hawkin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1623007110p2/60316715.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3236634650?book_show_action=true">Mar 18, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="W.L. Hawkin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="W.L. Hawkin" href="/user/show/60316715-w-l-hawkin">W.L. Hawkin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3236634650" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1193469560434007186">What a cool book! The title had me guessing but once the author revealed what it was all about it made so much sense. The genre still has me guessing . . . dark twisted romantic comedy? There are definitely dark moments involving several murdered men, some of them even nice. But I smiled my way through most of this charming read. It revolves around a quirky love triangle between Tara (our hero), Betsy (her besty bi friend--good play on words), and Glen, Tara&apos;s lover. Basically, when Tara&apos;s third</span>
  <span id="freeText1193469560434007186" style="display:none">What a cool book! The title had me guessing but once the author revealed what it was all about it made so much sense. The genre still has me guessing . . . dark twisted romantic comedy? There are definitely dark moments involving several murdered men, some of them even nice. But I smiled my way through most of this charming read. It revolves around a quirky love triangle between Tara (our hero), Betsy (her besty bi friend--good play on words), and Glen, Tara's lover. Basically, when Tara's third boyfriend dies, after she catches him messing around on her and gets mad at him, she begins to think she has the power to psychically kill men. Betsy introduces Tara to her spiritual world and the fun begins. The author has a blast with New Age stereotypes, but though I do psychic readings and use Motherpeace cards, I never felt mocked. I could only laugh. And when Tara turns her office into a meditation room, I started cleaning and looking at paint colors myself. I still might buy a beanbag meditation chair. Hmm . . . So, if you're looking for some smiles, some relief, and a light read, pick this one up. My only complaint is that I would have liked to have seen the antagonist brought to justice. But maybe that doesn't happen in romantic comedy. Maybe it's about happy (sort of) endings. I don't know. My killers generally don't walk away at the end of the book. </span>
  <a data-text-id="1193469560434007186" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


