    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2538570572" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2538570572" />
    <a title="Jason Lee" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/65100260-jason-lee"><img alt="Jason Lee" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1569897502p2/65100260.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2538570572?book_show_action=true">Sep 22, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jason Lee" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jason Lee" href="/user/show/65100260-jason-lee">Jason Lee</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2538570572" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13060815603244690398">An absolute delightful read from start to finish! I found myself not wanting to put the book down because I was addicted to finding out what happens to Tara and Betsy, yet I also didn&apos;t want the book to end because of how real the characters are. This book has a bit of everything: romance, spirituality, mystery, business &amp; marketing and personal development, all of which is nicely paced in the book. I particularly enjoyed the quirky moments between Tara and Betsy and how their friendship is so r</span>
  <span id="freeText13060815603244690398" style="display:none">An absolute delightful read from start to finish! I found myself not wanting to put the book down because I was addicted to finding out what happens to Tara and Betsy, yet I also didn't want the book to end because of how real the characters are. This book has a bit of everything: romance, spirituality, mystery, business &amp; marketing and personal development, all of which is nicely paced in the book. I particularly enjoyed the quirky moments between Tara and Betsy and how their friendship is so relatable on so many levels. I think we all know someone in our lives who are like either Tara or Betsy.<br /><br />Donna Barker cleverly weaves so many genres conveniently into her book. I found myself both entertained and educated which is so unique but she totally makes it work! If you're a budding entrepreneur struggling to get your business going, this book dabbles in it with nuggets of tips and inspiration. It's loaded with great stuff, including an ending that gives you an a-ha moment on how you see yourself and others. This book has it all and I highly recommend everyone to read MTAJL, you won't regret it. 5 out of 5 stars for the story and a perfect 5 to a highly gifted author.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13060815603244690398" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review2538570572">
